00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:06.690
Last day, Professor Ballinger
introduced you to Lewis who taught

00:05:06.690 --> 00:05:11.460
us that octet stability could be
achieved via electron sharing as an

00:05:11.460 --> 00:05:16.230
alternative to electron transfer.
And he coined the term covalent

00:05:16.230 --> 00:05:35.326
bonding. It means cooperative
sharing of valence electrons.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:05.000
That is what gets crunched down to
covalent bonding.

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:09.000
Pauling came along later and told
us that the electrons are not shared

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:13.000
equally, and this was important
because there were problems in

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:17.000
computing the bond energies of
heteronuclear molecules.

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:21.000
If you looked at heteronuclear
molecules and you wanted to compute

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:25.000
the bond energy,
you might start with the bond

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:29.000
energies of the two constituents.
And you would find that the bond

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:33.000
energy of the heteronuclear molecule
was nowhere on the average

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:56.920
of the two.
And that did not make sense.

00:05:56.920 --> 00:06:00.760
If I have one that's 400 kilojoules
per mole and another that's 200

00:06:00.760 --> 00:06:04.610
kilojoules per mole and I blend them,
how do I get 500 kilojoules per mole?

00:06:04.610 --> 00:06:08.460
That bothered people.
And Pauling came along and said the

00:06:08.460 --> 00:06:12.300
unequal sharing of electrons in a
covalent bond can explain that extra

00:06:12.300 --> 00:06:16.150
energy. And he coined the term
"polar covalency."

00:06:16.150 --> 00:06:36.033
And, in particular,
he introduced a quantitative measure.

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:23.840
This is why he gets the Nobel prize
and Lewis did not get the Nobel

00:06:23.840 --> 00:06:27.690
prize, although Lewis did brilliant
work, but Pauling's work was

00:06:27.690 --> 00:06:31.530
quantitative. He introduced the
concept of electronegativity which

00:06:31.530 --> 00:06:35.380
was a measure,
therefore, it is quantitative,

00:06:35.380 --> 00:06:39.230
of the atom's ability to attract
electrons within a covalent bond and

00:06:39.230 --> 00:06:43.070
developed a scale of
electronegativity.

00:06:43.070 --> 00:06:47.170
That is shown here.
And this looks a lot like the

00:06:47.170 --> 00:06:51.520
average valence electron energy
where the lowest values of

00:06:51.520 --> 00:06:55.880
electronegativity are in the
metallic zone and the highest values

00:06:55.880 --> 00:07:00.230
of electronegativity are on the
nonmetallic zone.

00:07:00.230 --> 00:07:04.580
Think about it. If this is a
measure of the ability of an

00:07:04.580 --> 00:07:08.930
electron to be pulled in a covalent
bond, so if I have H here and F here

00:07:08.930 --> 00:07:13.290
and F is more electronegative than H,
and so the electrons,

00:07:13.290 --> 00:07:17.640
instead of being shared equally,
I am going to show them over here as

00:07:17.640 --> 00:07:36.080
if to say fluorine is
hogging the electron.

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:25.370
It makes sense.
If this is metallic,

00:07:25.370 --> 00:07:28.740
it is a good electron donor.
Well, if it is a good electron

00:07:28.740 --> 00:07:32.120
donor in an electron transfer
reaction, if the same element finds

00:07:32.120 --> 00:07:35.490
itself in a covalent bond,
it is going to be a good electron

00:07:35.490 --> 00:07:38.870
donor, although it is not full
transfer. Likewise,

00:07:38.870 --> 00:07:42.240
the element that is a good electron
acceptor in an electron transfer

00:07:42.240 --> 00:07:45.620
reaction is going to be the element
that is going to hog the electrons

00:07:45.620 --> 00:08:05.773
in a covalent bond.
So there is some consistency here.

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:33.000
And you see where the most
electronegative elements are,

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:37.000
and fluorine is the most
electronegative of the active

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:41.000
elements. I know neon has a higher
yet electronegativity,

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:45.000
but normally it is inert.
So how do we use this

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:49.000
electronegativity?
Well, I mentioned to you that there

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:53.000
was this mystery.
Let's go back and review one of

00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:57.000
these. This is the homonuclear bond
energy for hydrogen in pure hydrogen.

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:21.810
There we have perfect covalency.
Both hydrogens are going to share

00:08:21.810 --> 00:08:27.450
equally. We don't have two
different species of hydrogen here,

00:08:27.450 --> 00:08:33.090
so the electrons are perfectly
shared. And this turns out to have

00:08:33.090 --> 00:08:38.720
a bond strength of 435 kilojoules
per mole. And,

00:08:38.720 --> 00:08:44.360
likewise, if we look at fluorine in
its diatomic molecule,

00:08:44.360 --> 00:09:03.053
it is 160 kilojoules per mole.
And you have the bond energy in HF.

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:34.000
Just so that we are clear,
this is the bond in this compound.

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:38.000
As we see a little bit later, I
could talk about the carbon-hydrogen

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:42.000
bond in methane where there is a
plurality of bonds.

00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:46.000
In this case, there is only the one
bond but I just want to get the

00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:50.000
formulas. And so this is the H-F
bond in HF. It is nowhere on this

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:54.000
interval. And this is what puzzled
people. It is 569 kilojoules per

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:58.000
mole. So there is something extra
going on. And so what Pauling gave

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:23.750
us was a formula.
He said if you take the XY bond

00:09:23.750 --> 00:09:31.250
energy starting with the bond
energies XX, and YY bond energies,

00:09:31.250 --> 00:09:38.750
this is how to make sense of it.
What Pauling taught us was that the

00:09:38.750 --> 00:09:46.250
energy of the XY bond is equal to
the average. We are going to start

00:09:46.250 --> 00:10:04.133
with the average.
That is a good place to start.

00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:34.500
And he defined the average in terms
of not the sum divided by two,

00:09:34.500 --> 00:09:37.500
but he chose the geometric mean.
So you take the square root of the

00:09:37.500 --> 00:09:40.500
product. In fact,
there are some very old books that

00:09:40.500 --> 00:09:43.500
show this as the average,
the sum divided by two arithmetic

00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:46.500
mean, but the modern practice is to
use the geometric mean.

00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:49.500
And then he said there is a second
term here, a contribution to the

00:09:49.500 --> 00:09:52.500
unequal sharing.
And to measure the intensity of

00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:55.500
unequal sharing,
we take the difference in

00:09:55.500 --> 00:09:58.500
electronegativity,
which I am going to use the Greek

00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:22.570
symbol chi for.
This is lower case chi.

00:10:22.570 --> 00:10:27.710
I will take chi X minus chi Y.
And the functionality goes as the

00:10:27.710 --> 00:10:32.850
square of the difference in
electronegativity.

00:10:32.850 --> 00:10:37.990
And the prefactor is 96.
when you want to get a result in

00:10:37.990 --> 00:10:43.140
kilojoules per mole.
Let's go through this calculation

00:10:43.140 --> 00:10:48.280
for HF. If we look at 435 times 160,
take the square root of that,

00:10:48.280 --> 00:10:53.420
we will end up with 264 kilojoules
per mole, which sensibly lies

00:10:53.420 --> 00:10:58.440
between these two values.
And then this second term,

00:10:58.440 --> 00:11:03.330
if we go to the Periodic Table,
we will find that the value here for

00:11:03.330 --> 00:11:08.220
hydrogen is 2.
and the value for fluorine is 3.

00:11:08.220 --> 00:11:13.110
8. You plug all of this in and you
get 344 kilojoules per mole,

00:11:13.110 --> 00:11:31.086
which then sums to 608. Now,
608 is not 569.

00:10:58.000 --> 00:11:22.570
But, remember,
this is a very rough estimate.

00:11:22.570 --> 00:11:27.140
But the beauty in this calculation
is it shows that this concept of

00:11:27.140 --> 00:11:31.710
electron sharing in an unequal
manner is sound and it gets you into

00:11:31.710 --> 00:11:36.280
the right ballpark.
And so Pauling went further and

00:11:36.280 --> 00:11:40.850
said this is the purely covalent
component. This is purely covalent

00:11:40.850 --> 00:11:45.420
because all it is is homonuclear
bond energies.

00:11:45.420 --> 00:12:04.840
Homonuclear means both elements in
the molecule are the same.

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:35.000
There is no homoelemental.
They say homonuclear. So this is

00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:40.000
purely covalent.
And what is this?

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:45.000
He said this is partial ionic
character. Why did he choose that

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:50.000
term? Well, I like to think of it
as I have this sort of sharing meter.

00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:55.000
And I will give you the extremes.
If I look at a homonuclear molecule

00:11:55.000 --> 00:12:00.000
such as molecular hydrogen,
this is perfect sharing.

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:26.660
If this is my sharing meter,
this is my electron sharing meter.

00:12:26.660 --> 00:12:33.330
It is right at 12:00. Now, if I
get over here,

00:12:33.330 --> 00:12:39.990
HF, I know that fluorine is hogging
the electron, so it is not equal

00:12:39.990 --> 00:12:46.660
sharing. It is over here.
This is pure covalency. This is

00:12:46.660 --> 00:12:51.930
polar covalency.
And why did he call it polar

00:12:51.930 --> 00:12:55.790
covalency? Because,
if you look at this molecule,

00:12:55.790 --> 00:12:59.660
you say that, well, the electrons
are a little bit closer to the right

00:12:59.660 --> 00:13:03.530
than to the left so the charge is
not uniformly distributed.

00:13:03.530 --> 00:13:07.390
The molecule is net neutral,
but this right end is a little bit

00:13:07.390 --> 00:13:11.260
more negative and the left end is a
little bit more positive.

00:13:11.260 --> 00:13:15.130
And in physics, when physicists
want to say "a little bit of,

00:13:15.130 --> 00:13:35.860
they write lower case delta. That
is physics talk for a little bit of.

00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:23.570
So this is a little bit negative and
this is a little bit positive,

00:13:23.570 --> 00:13:28.140
which means I could model this by
drawing a dipole.

00:13:28.140 --> 00:13:32.710
This is a dipole.
It has a negative end and a

00:13:32.710 --> 00:13:37.280
positive end and it has certain
properties. If we put a dipole that

00:13:37.280 --> 00:13:41.850
has the freedom to move,
we put that dipole in an electric

00:13:41.850 --> 00:13:46.420
field, it will align itself with the
field lines. Because this is a

00:13:46.420 --> 00:14:06.306
dipole, he chose the pole part of
dipole to give us polar covalency.

00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:55.460
And what is the ultimate?
What is the extreme of unequal

00:13:55.460 --> 00:13:59.920
sharing? It is electron transfer.
So this is perfect sharing, unequal

00:13:59.920 --> 00:14:04.380
sharing. And here the electrons are
actually donated,

00:14:04.380 --> 00:14:08.840
so this becomes F minus.
This is denuded of an electron,

00:14:08.840 --> 00:14:13.300
it is Na plus. And so, this one
here, I am going to say let's bury

00:14:13.300 --> 00:14:17.760
the needle on this one.
This is the ultimate in unequal

00:14:17.760 --> 00:14:22.720
sharing and this is ionic.
This is ionic bonding.

00:14:22.720 --> 00:14:28.180
So you can see that polar covalency
is a tendency towards ionic bonding.

00:14:28.180 --> 00:14:33.630
And that is why Pauling called this
partial ionic character.

00:14:33.630 --> 00:14:39.080
And he actually quantified it.
He quantified it by this formula.

00:14:39.080 --> 00:14:44.540
He said that the percent ionic
character, and this is within a bond,

00:14:44.540 --> 00:15:01.680
not for a compound, for
a covalent bond.

00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:55.630
He said that is going to equal one
minus the exponential.

00:14:55.630 --> 00:15:01.270
This is just base e, natural
logarithm. E to the power of minus

00:15:01.270 --> 00:15:06.900
one-quarter times the difference in
electronegativity squared.

00:15:06.900 --> 00:15:12.540
It is this thing again. You see
the difference in electronegativity,

00:15:12.540 --> 00:15:18.180
square it, multiply it by
one-quarter and raise

00:15:18.180 --> 00:15:22.930
that to the power e.
Subtract that from one,

00:15:22.930 --> 00:15:26.790
multiply it by 100 and you have
something between zero and 100.

00:15:26.790 --> 00:15:30.660
And I think there is some evidence
of that here. This is right off

00:15:30.660 --> 00:15:34.530
your Periodic Table.
If you look up in the corner of

00:15:34.530 --> 00:15:38.390
your Periodic Table on one of the
sides, they have actually tabulated

00:15:38.390 --> 00:15:42.260
this for you. I have rewritten the
formula here. And there are two

00:15:42.260 --> 00:15:46.130
different scales of ionic character.
One by Pauling. Actually, there

00:15:46.130 --> 00:16:05.126
are more than two. But
they show these, too.

00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:55.380
There is Pauling and there is Hannay
and Smyth. Here is Pauling.

00:15:55.380 --> 00:16:00.760
And we could do this for our
compound here,

00:16:00.760 --> 00:16:06.150
HF. For HF, just for grins and
chuckles, let's do it.

00:16:06.150 --> 00:16:11.530
The electronegativity of fluorine
is 3.98 and the electronegativity of

00:16:11.530 --> 00:16:16.920
H is 2.20 on this scale.
And so, if you plug these values

00:16:16.920 --> 00:16:22.300
into this formula,
that will give you the percent ionic

00:16:22.300 --> 00:16:27.090
character for the H-F bond.
And I want to make sure that you

00:16:27.090 --> 00:16:31.270
don't think that this is the percent
ionic character of the compound,

00:16:31.270 --> 00:16:35.450
so I am going to be really
fastidious here and indicate that I

00:16:35.450 --> 00:16:39.630
am talking about the H-F bond.
If you plug into this formula here,

00:16:39.630 --> 00:16:43.810
you end up with 56%. And that has
already been tabulated up there in

00:16:43.810 --> 00:17:02.286
the nomograph. You will
see if you get --

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:53.810
I think the delta here is 1.
8, which is roughly 1.8. And there

00:16:53.810 --> 00:16:59.630
you see the 56.
Just to give you a sense of what

00:16:59.630 --> 00:17:05.450
that means, if the 264 figure is
pure covalency and the 344 is

00:17:05.450 --> 00:17:11.270
partial ionic character,
what fraction of the 608 is 344?

00:17:11.270 --> 00:17:17.090
344, which is partial ionic
character, divided by

00:17:17.090 --> 00:17:21.760
608 times 100 is 57%.
So it makes sense.

00:17:21.760 --> 00:17:25.290
That is good. We can do all sorts
of things with this.

00:17:25.290 --> 00:17:28.820
So I indicated the molecule.
There is another orthography that

00:17:28.820 --> 00:17:32.350
is used to indicate dipole.
You can use delta minus, delta plus.

00:17:32.350 --> 00:17:35.880
Some people like to use an arrow,
and the arrow points in the

00:17:35.880 --> 00:17:39.410
direction of the more
